2013-05-11  Added abiltiy to run Raspi_Gtalk_Robot on startup of RaspberryPI
You will need to do the following - copied from http://raspbpi.blogspot.co.uk/2012/12/raspi-python-script-on-startup.html

copy the Gtalk file in your RaspberyPi's /etc/int.d directory or create it
sudo nano /etc/init.d/gtalk

Change Permisision to make it executable
chmod 755 /etc/init.d/gtalk

Update your services
update-rc.d doorboot defaults

Test your script
sudo /etc/init.d/gtalk start

